attributes.Name: Senate House
attributes.Caption: First place one goes through when entering Wits. Registrations, fees and cashiers office. Also houses the Vice Chancelor's office

attributes.Name: Geography and Archaeology
attributes.Caption: The School of Geography, Archaeology and Environmental Studies is one of the most productive research units at Wits. Staff members contribute regularly to local and international publications and are members of the editorial boards of many prestigious journals. The School has an excellent reputation both locally and internationally as one of the leaders in African scholarship on issues such as sustainability, climate change, urban social and environmental justice, tourism and development.

attributes.Name: Paloesciences
attributes.Caption: The Evolutionary Studies Institute. The richness and completeness of South Africa�s fossil record makes it a prime laboratory for studying the origins of species through time, including human origins.

attributes.Name: Geosciences
attributes.Caption: With 18 academic and 30 Honorary staff, it is the largest and most diverse academic Earth Science institution in southern Africa and the only one offering specialist Honours degrees in Geophysics and Palaeontology, in addition to Geology, Geochemistry and Environmental Earth Science. The School leads several initiatives for geosciences research and training nationally and on the African continent.

attributes.Name: Chemistry
attributes.Caption: The Wits School of Chemistry consists of over 60 permanent academic and technical staff, as well as a number of honorary staff, and around 100 Post-Graduate students and Post-Doctoral Fellows.

attributes.Name: Molecular and Cell Biology
attributes.Caption: The School of Molecular and Cell Biology (MCB) within the Faculty of Science at the University of the Witwatersrand proudly offers cutting-edge teaching and research across diverse subject areas. The school has three main focus areas: Biochemistry & Cell Biology, Genetics & Developmental Biology and Microbiology & Biotechnology.

attributes.Name: Chamber of Mines
attributes.Caption: The study of engineering involves the conservation and development of the earth�s natural, agricultural and mineral resources in order to serve humanity�s needs. In addition, engineering plays a vital role in the survival of the South African and international economies. We often take for granted our roads, bridges, buildings, cars, aeroplanes, fuels, electricity, television and telephones, but none of these would be possible without engineers.

attributes.Name: Law
attributes.Caption: The Oliver Schreiner School of Law is recognized as one of the top law schools in the country, with a reputation for leading edge research, active public engagement, excellent teaching and rigorous training.

attributes.Name: Accounting
attributes.Caption: The Wits School of Accountacy attracts and produces some of the country�s best financial minds, making it the first choice for many individuals seeking to pursue a career in the field of Accountancy. The School consistently produces some of the top performers in the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (SAICA) and Independent Regulatory Board of Auditors (IRBA) Qualifying Examinations.

attributes.Name: The Built Environment
attributes.Caption: Degrees in the Built Environment address the social, spatial and infrastructural needs of a transforming South Africa. This includes the degrees in Architecture, Urban and Regional Planning, Property Studies and Quantity Surveying. The delivery of affordable housing, the development of rural and urban environments, and meeting other social and physical challenges form the basis of the teaching, learning and research programmes that are offered by this particular Faculty.

attributes.Name: School of Arts
attributes.Caption: Through advancing excellence in research, teaching and learning, the Wits School of Arts combines critical inquiry with artistic practice in ways that engage in transformative ways with our contemporary urban, African and global contexts.

attributes.Name: Wits Plus
attributes.Caption: If life and your career is a full-time job and you can�t study full-time but you need to learn more to earn more or advance yourself then WITS Plus is for you!

attributes.Name: Waternweiler Library
attributes.Caption: Waternweiler Library is a Helping Hand for Arts, Drama,Music And Film Students. It has an important electronic journal subscription to the Oxford suite of resources, aimed at the Arts and Social Sciences disciplines.

attributes.Name: William Cullen Library
attributes.Caption: The William Cullen Library is situated on the east campus of the University. The library was named after Dr. William Cullen (1867-1948) - Chemist & Metallurgist.

attributes.Name: The Plametarium
attributes.Caption: The planetarium serves as an academic and educational centre for scholars, researchers and academics who study astronomy. The planetarium hosts about 70 000 visitors per year who come to view numerous displays, and engage in tours, lectures and workshops.

attributes.Name: Origins Centre
attributes.Caption: Opened by President Thabo Mbeki in 2006, the Origins Centre is a world-class museum dedicated to exploring and celebrating the history of modern humankind, telling the story of the emergence of human beings and humanity in southern Africa.

attributes.Name: Wits Arts Museum
attributes.Caption: Wits Art Museum is home to an extraordinary collection of African art, including contemporary and historical art from South Africa and art from West and Central Africa. It hosts a dynamic program of events and art exhibitions. The Museum is one of Johannesburg's premier tourist attractions, along with the Apartheid Museum and Constitution Hill. It is part of the Wits University Cultural Precinct, just three blocks from Nelson Mandela Bridge. WAM is in the hip, regenerating area of Braamfontein, which is also home to many students, interesting shops and places to eat. The WAM Cafe is a fun place to meet friends and enjoy delicious food and coffee.

attributes.Name: The Matrix
attributes.Caption: A student mall, the Matrix, originally housed 26 leisure and convenience outlets. It continues to grow with the introduction of new shops and food spots.

attributes.Name: Old Mutual Sports Hall
attributes.Caption: Houses a diverse range of sports and facilities which include: Gymnastics, Weights, Badminton, Karate, Mountain Wall, Yuishinkai Kobujutsu and Tai Chi

attributes.Name: Great Hall
attributes.Caption: Corinthian columns and classic monumental architecture make the Wits Great Hall an archetypal university building. It was originally opened in 1934. The Great Hall seats up to 1035, has a rich heritage that dates back to the world premiere of the SA musical, King Kong and beyond. Today, it is usually used for Graduations, Prize Givings and special lectures.
